<br>
Imagine writing a letter in MS Word when every time you press a key it does a hard write to disk instead of just storing in memory. Now imagine 3k people all using MS Word and storing every keypress to the same set of disks instead of memory. There would be severe performance degredation - even if it were just limited to looting (imagine how many loots/trades occur in any given minute across a server). <br>
<br>
Yes there are answers though. A /save command is a good idea though it can be done manually as I suggested through zoning or camping. It just takes 30 sec or so longer this way.<br>
<br>
