<br>
<br>
My guild did an impromptu BoT tower run.  Three bosses were a waste of virtual space (as usual), the fourth was the motherlode.  Two Stormrider signets, best loot our casters have seen in months.<br>
<br>
The boss drops and we are cleaning up the last add.  No more than 45 seconds after the boss kill, I start getting spammed with people dropping raid.  I had time to wonder &quot;Ok, what did I miss?&quot; before &quot;YOU HAVE BEEN DISCONNECTED&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
You guessed it, server crash.  Veeshan came back up in about fifteen minutes.  Unfortunately, there was a rollback.  Moreso, they managed to roll me back to the exact instant I was standing at a spawn point for the only see invis giant type in the whole damn tower.<br>
<br>
How do they do that??<br>
<br>
Oddly enough, the boss corpse was still there.  One of our SoS rogues looted the rings, petitioned and got them moved to the appropriate wizards after about 14 hours.  40 minutes waiting for the rest of the raid to GY, rezz, med up and off to bed.<br>
<br>
The most surprising thing was that a character rollback was necessary, the tower was fully popped yet the boss corpse was still in game.<br>
<br>
Some very strange dbase work going on...... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1>General EQ Discussion</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

